JO  - Econometrica
JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 2231
EP  - 2292
VL  - 83
IS  - 6
KW  - OTC markets
KW  - derivatives
KW  - search
KW  - entry and exit
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA11477
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We develop a parsimonious model to study the equilibrium and socially optimal decisions of banks to enter, trade in, and possibly exit, an OTC market. Although we endow all banks with the same trading technology, banks' optimal entry and trading decisions endogenously lead to a realistic market structure composed of dealers and customers with distinct trading patterns. We decompose banks' entry incentives into incentives to hedge risk and incentives to make intermediation profits. We show that dealer banks enter more than is socially optimal. In the face of large negative shocks, they may also exit more than is socially optimal when markets are not perfectly resilient.
ER  - 

